name: "Slipstreams" Pattern Tote Bag
description:
Hand-sewn tote bag digitally printed with "Slipstreams" hand-painted pattern on heavy cotton/linen canvas. 

Bag is unlined and measures 13 x 15 x 3". Straps are 1" wide and 15" long from the top of the bag.

Only two of these have been made and each is slightly different due to placement of the pattern. A wonderful summer tote!

name: "Fischaugen" Pattern Reversible Collar
description:
Hand-sewn reversible detached collar digitally printed with "Fischaugen" ("Fish Eyes") hand-painted pattern. Reverses from purple colorway to orange on cotton poplin fabric. Collar ties with a grey grosgrain ribbon, and can be sized as needed.

Collar is 3.5" wide with a curved neckline of about 12.5". The grosgrain ties are around 15" long. 

These collars are great for adding interest to an outfit! Only two were ever (and ever will be) made.

name: Koshka Zine #1
description:
KOSHKA brings you the best in art, culture, and ideas from an Eastern European perspective. After months of conducting interviews, designing, sourcing writers and sourcing printing materials (all done while doing my MFA coursework in the Interdisciplinary Book and Paper Arts program at Columbia College Chicago), I’m happy to say that issue 01 is ready for you to get your paws on! In addition to being created by myself and a small group of dedicated friends, the printed publication was “hand printed” on a Heidelberg GTO offset press at Columbia College’s Center for Book and Paper Arts by myself and Kathi Beste. We also spent two days folding, collating, stapling, and trimming by hand, so this is truly a handmade affair!

KOSHKA 01 has two-color cover art by Sanya Glisic, 40 b+w pages, and a 5.5 x 8.5” stature. It is printed on Mohawk Superfine i-tone white 80lb text (interior) and Mohawk Superfine Softwhite 80lb cover.

KOSHKA 01 features:

+Monika Bukowska (Brilliant Pebbles)

+Rich Szczepanski (Well Slept Film Fest, Silent Scones, the English Softhearts)

+Mikelis Bastiks (Asketic, Burtustype.com, plikums.lv)

+PetPunk aka Andrius Kirvela and Gediminas Siaulys (graphics and motion)

+ David Schilter (kuš! Baltic comics journal)

+ Sanya Glisic (print and illustration)

+Tin Can Forest, aka Marek Colek and Pat Shewchuk (Baba Yaga and the Wolf, Pohadky)

+A culinary investigation of mamaliga (Romanian polenta) by Sara K.

+Reminisces on teaching Russian to Chicago Public School students by Jonathan Sanchez-Leos

name: Koshka Zine #2
description:
Koshka Zine returns with its second issue, delving into the theme "Homesick and Hungry", where food, culture, and nostalgia converge on a Central and Eastern European mindspace. 

This issue features:

+ A photographic look into DIY Czech Greenhouses by Riley A. Arthur

+ Illustrations from granny's kitchen by Csenge Csato

+ A visual parody of Eastern European store shelves by Robert Krums

+ Personal narrative on being gay and foreign in Russia by Jonathan Sanchez Leos

+ A homesick comic by Milena Simeonova

+ Oma's Recipes and an illustrated product guide of Eastern treats by Kaitlin Kostus

Cover illustrations by Kaitlin Kostus. 11x17", 16 pages, black and white offset print on newsprint with red spot color on front and back covers. Released April 2012.

name: 'DDR Kamera Praktica' hand-printed art object
description:
Print object, sculpture, and wearable in one! Print multiple replicating a camera from the German Democratic Republic, comprised of a linocut backed with board and a strap made from bias tape and hook-and-eye closures. Created in an edition of 4 with two in tan and two in green. Each camera comes inside a hand relief printed GDR shopping bag with a replicated slogan translating to "bought well, bought gladly". Camera can be worn if you so choose, so you can not take photos of things that don't really exist! Signed and edition number noted on back. 

Camera: 5.5 x 4" with 16" long strap.
Bag: 8.5 x 11.25"

name: Screenprinted Baltic Folk Pattern cotton kitchen rags/tea towels
description:
A Baltic (that's Latvia, Lithuania, or Estonia) folk pattern hand-silkscreened onto a set of kitchen towels. The image was hand-painted into the screen and printed in a dark wood brown. Each towel is 20 x 26" in size.

Each towel set includes TWO 100% cotton woven towels in white with forest green contrast around the perimeter. The towels also have loops in one corner so they can be hung from cabinetry.

Launder to your liking.  Welcome wear and tear. 

These three sets are the last out of an edition of 14, and they will never be made again!

Comes from a smoke-free environment.

name: Harvest Halo Kerchief / Head Scarf from upcycled vintage floral pillowcase fabric
description:
Hand screenprinted wheat circle on a 22x22" square of upcycled vintage pillowcase fabrics. Exact fabric content unknown, but it is a lightweight woven. There is a single row of contrast stitching around the perimeter of the scarf.

Inspired by images of Soviet women, the scarf can be worn on your head, around your neck, as a dog kerchief, and they are even nice on small end tables as a tablecloth. 


These six kerchiefs are the last remaining from a variable edition of 14. They will never be made again!

Launder to your liking. Welcome wear and tear.

From a smoke-free environment.

name: Czar Nicolai Royal Tea Drawing
description: Original drawing by Kaitlin Kostus of a box of Czar Nicolai "Royal Tea". Marker and pen on pure white drawing paper, 8.5 x 11". Drawn in 2012, this drawing appeared in Koshka Zine #2. Signed and dated on back with pencil.

name: 'Meska Siaureje' Lithuanian Chocolate Drawing
description: Original drawing by Kaitlin Kostus of a Lithuanian chocolate candy with a polar bear on the wrapper. Marker and pen on pure white drawing paper, 8.5 x 11". Drawn in 2012, this drawing appeared in Koshka Zine #2. Signed and dated on back with pencil.

name: Finnish Fazer Salmiakki Drawing
description: Original drawing by Kaitlin Kostus of a box of Finnish Salmiakki candy. Marker and pen on pure white heavyweight watercolor paper, 7.5 x 10". Drawn in 2012, never published. Signed and dated on back with pencil.

name: Ukrainian Chocolates Original Drawing
description: Original drawing by Kaitlin Kostus of a pair of Ukrainian chocolate candies. Marker and pen on pure white drawing paper, 8.5 x 11". Drawn in 2012, this drawing appeared in Koshka Zine #2. Signed and dated on back with pencil.

name: 'Kalendārs/Kalendorius'--original sculpture
description:
A work from the exhibition "The One Who Rises" shown at Woman Made Gallery in Chicago in the Spring of 2012. Using materials evoking nature new Baltic "artifacts" are created in the 21st century. These antlers are a calendar, though how the antler points and colored bars demarcate time, and in what measure or context, remains in the annals of what could perhaps be ancient or recent history.

Acrylic gouache on deer antlers with jute twine, base of antler is 10" with main points around 12", twine about 18" when doubled, as shown. Piece can easily hang from a heavyweight nail or hook. by Kaitlin Kostus.

**IMPORTANT SHIPPING INFO: This item is currently only available via pick-up to Chicago area residents ONLY, as I don't trust UPS to ship this item and cannot afford a more reputable service. Pick-up can be scheduled when payment is made. Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions.

Acrylic gouache and graphite on wood panel, with edges "gilded" in gold paint, 12 x 12 x 0.5". Titled, signed, and dated on back in ink. by Kaitlin Kostus

This item will ship via courier (UPS or FedEx). Painting includes a metal french cleat attached to back of painting and the twin to attach to your wall.
